task_description: Facing the building to your West (approx. 258°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roof.
I still cannot see the top of the building, so I need to tilt my view further up to see the roofline.
Now that I can see the top of the building, I need to look down to see the base to get a full sense of its height.

Having viewed both the top and the base of the building, I can now estimate its height by counting the floors; I count approximately 16 floors, and assuming a standard height of 3.5 to 4 meters per floor for a commercial building, the total height is likely around 60 meters.
